    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>University Hospital, Bonn</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Former studies revealed a distinct pattern of changes in circulation during deliberate apnea.
      Blood pressure rises significantly often accompanied by bradycardia. Further studies
      confirmed a massive increase of total vascular resistance as it also happens in shock to
      maintain perfusion of heart, lung and brain. This study is to determine the exact alterations
      of the cardiac function during this reaction, show the redistribution of blood volume in
      apnea and evaluate possible longterm effects on the central nervous system caused by repeated
      apnea via magnetic resonance imaging.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
